WEBVTT

00:01.938 --> 00:02.937
(LAVA BUBBLING)

00:04.000 --> 00:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:29.999 --> 00:31.365
(ROARING)

00:34.737 --> 00:36.587
I'll be honest, Ferb.

00:36.588 --> 00:38.438
I'm having a hard time
putting a positive spin
on this.

00:38.441 --> 00:40.140
But I guess
that's life, huh?

00:40.142 --> 00:42.660
One minute,
you're having
the best day ever,

00:42.661 --> 00:45.179
the next, you're being fed
to a monster the size of
a two-car garage.

00:45.181 --> 00:48.849
Yeah? Well,
welcome to my life.

00:48.851 --> 00:52.419
Huh. And everything
started out so well
this morning.

01:13.276 --> 01:13.874
(CHATTERING)

01:15.911 --> 01:17.111
Good morning, Perry.

01:17.113 --> 01:19.280
Now that's the way
to wake up.

01:19.282 --> 01:20.781
This is gonna be
the best day ever.

01:20.783 --> 01:24.184
<i> ♪ We consider</i>
<i> every day a plus</i>

01:24.186 --> 01:26.820
<i> ♪ To spend it</i>
<i> with a platypus</i>

01:26.822 --> 01:31.458
<i> ♪ We're always so</i>
<i> ecstatic</i>
<i> 'Cause he's semi-aquatic</i>

01:31.460 --> 01:34.161
<i> ♪ Our Ornithorhynchus</i>
<i> anatinus</i>

01:34.163 --> 01:37.832
<i> ♪ Brings smiles</i>
<i> to the both of us</i>

01:37.833 --> 01:41.502
<i> ♪ Life's never</i>
<i> fuddy-duddy</i>
<i> With our web-footed buddy</i>

01:41.504 --> 01:43.203
<i> ♪ When we're</i>
<i> brushing our teeth</i>
<i> It's better</i>

01:43.205 --> 01:46.473
<i> ♪ Tying our shoes</i>
<i> It's better</i>

01:46.475 --> 01:48.942
<i> ♪ Combing our hair</i>
<i> It's better</i>

01:48.944 --> 01:51.412
<i> ♪ Like we're a cheese</i>
<i> sandwich</i>
<i> And he's the cheddar</i>

01:51.414 --> 01:53.981
<i> ♪ Blinking our eyes</i>
<i> It's better</i>

01:53.983 --> 01:56.283
<i> ♪ Breathing in and out</i>
<i> So much better</i>

01:56.285 --> 01:58.819
<i> ♪ Sitting in a chair</i>
<i> It's better</i>

01:58.821 --> 02:01.455
<i> ♪ And taking a bath</i>
<i> Just a little bit wetter</i>

02:01.457 --> 02:06.193
<i> ♪ Every day is such a</i>
<i> dream</i>
<i> When it's started with</i>
<i> a monotreme</i>

02:06.195 --> 02:09.863
<i> ♪ He's duck-billed</i>
<i> and he's beaver-tailed</i>
<i> and hairy</i>

02:09.865 --> 02:10.997
<i> ♪ You know that he's</i>
<i> hairy</i>

02:11.000 --> 02:14.335
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with Perry</i>

02:14.337 --> 02:16.837
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with Perry</i>

02:16.839 --> 02:19.106
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with Perry</i>

02:19.108 --> 02:21.542
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with Perry</i>

02:21.544 --> 02:23.778
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with Perry</i>

02:23.779 --> 02:26.013
<i> ♪ Everything's</i>
<i> better with Perry</i>
<i> Everything's better with</i>
<i> Perry</i>

02:26.015 --> 02:31.352
<i> ♪ It's better</i>
<i> And we just want</i>
<i> to tell you, Perry</i>

02:31.354 --> 02:34.254
<i> ♪ Everything's better</i>
<i> with you</i>

02:34.256 --> 02:35.456
<i> ♪ Better with you ♪</i>

02:35.458 --> 02:37.424
(CHATTERING)

02:37.426 --> 02:38.926
Good morning, boys.

02:38.928 --> 02:40.527
Happy anniversary, Perry.

02:40.529 --> 02:43.864
Oh, that's right!
Gosh. I can't believe
it's been five years.

02:43.866 --> 02:45.499
I remember the day
we first got you.

02:47.036 --> 02:49.203
Come on, kids.
Pick out any pet you want.

02:49.205 --> 02:52.039
Look, Phineas,
this one's
looking at you!

02:52.041 --> 02:53.340
And this one's
looking at you, Ferb.

02:55.544 --> 02:57.411
Why won't anything
look at me?

02:57.412 --> 02:59.279
Ferb! This one's looking
at
both of us at the same
time.

02:59.281 --> 03:01.515
(CHATTERING)

03:02.885 --> 03:04.485
That thing?
You're kidding, right?

03:04.487 --> 03:06.253
Is there something
I can do for you?

03:06.254 --> 03:08.020
Yes. We'd like
that one, please.

03:08.023 --> 03:09.923
You'd like to adopt
a platypus?

03:09.925 --> 03:11.291
Is that what it is?
Well, yes.

03:11.293 --> 03:13.277
May we have him, please?
Okay.

03:13.278 --> 03:15.262
What would you even
name a platypus?

03:15.264 --> 03:17.898
PHINEAS: <i> Of course,</i>
<i> Ferb and I knew exactly</i>
<i> what to call you.</i>

03:17.900 --> 03:19.266
BOTH: Bartholemew!

03:19.268 --> 03:21.001
(CHATTERING)

03:21.003 --> 03:22.536
And then when
we got you home,

03:22.538 --> 03:25.539
we renamed you Perry
and gave you this locket.

03:25.541 --> 03:27.908
Look how young
we all were.

03:27.910 --> 03:29.476
Hey, Jeremy.
You wanna go
to the mall?

03:29.478 --> 03:31.378
You know, I'd love to,

03:31.380 --> 03:34.281
but my dad's taking me
to check out his old
college today.

03:34.282 --> 03:37.183
Booyah! Go Polecats!
Booyah!

03:37.186 --> 03:39.353
He's already set up
an interview with
an academic advisor.

03:39.355 --> 03:41.305
Can you believe that?

03:41.306 --> 03:43.256
Gee, Jeremy, I forgot
you're a whole year
older than me.

03:43.259 --> 03:45.592
A trip to college?
That's...
That's really great.

03:45.594 --> 03:50.030
Okay, well,
I'll talk to
you later. Bye.

03:50.032 --> 03:52.332
Oh, Jeremy!
In the blink of an eye,

03:52.334 --> 03:53.634
you'll be moving on
to the next phase
of your life.

03:53.636 --> 03:56.403
<i> You'll be</i>
<i> going to college</i>

03:56.405 --> 03:58.539
<i> and wearing tweed jackets</i>
<i> with patches on the</i>
<i> elbows.</i>

03:58.541 --> 04:00.974
<i> You'll be so mature.</i>

04:00.976 --> 04:03.043
And look at me.
I'm a child!

04:03.045 --> 04:04.778
Jeremy, you'll see.
I can mature.

04:04.779 --> 04:06.512
Starting with taking
this silly photo off.

04:06.515 --> 04:10.517
(GASPS) Mr. Miggins!
Have you been there
the whole time?

04:10.519 --> 04:12.686
All right, looks like
the pitcher's ready.
And batter up!

04:15.391 --> 04:16.990
Batter, batter,
batter, swing!

04:16.992 --> 04:19.259
Yes, sports fans,

04:19.261 --> 04:21.478
that may be the best hit
ever in the history of
platypult baseball.

04:21.478 --> 04:23.696
And the crowd exhales
loudly
through their mouths.

04:23.699 --> 04:25.399
(MIMICS CROWD ROARING)

04:28.137 --> 04:31.171
And Fletcher
snags the pop fly.
He's out!

04:31.173 --> 04:33.390
Hi, Phineas!
What you doing?

04:33.391 --> 04:35.608
Turning Perry's
involuntary reflex
into a sporting event.

04:35.611 --> 04:37.611
Hi, Perry, can I try?

04:37.613 --> 04:39.980
Whoa, momma!
Nice shot, Isabella.

04:39.982 --> 04:41.448
Did someone
lose a ball?

04:41.450 --> 04:43.016
Yeah, we were just
playing platypult.

04:43.018 --> 04:44.618
I love
platypus-themed sports.

04:44.619 --> 04:46.219
You know,
if we had two Perrys,

04:46.222 --> 04:48.422
we could put a net
between them

04:48.424 --> 04:50.591
and play
platypult badminton.
Who's Annette?

04:50.593 --> 04:52.493
Ferb, that's it!
I know what we're
gonna do today.

04:52.495 --> 04:54.061
No, seriously.
Who's Annette?

04:56.065 --> 04:58.232
Okay, everyone,
I think the tail
is all set.

04:58.234 --> 04:59.633
I'll just go check
with the foreman.

04:59.635 --> 05:00.767
He's gone!

05:00.769 --> 05:02.236
Hey, where's Perry?

05:02.238 --> 05:05.772
Did he really slip away?
On his anniversary?

05:05.774 --> 05:07.441
Sometimes it seems
like Perry's missed

05:07.443 --> 05:10.611
every single cool thing
we've done all summer
long.

05:10.613 --> 05:12.513
I guess he can do
whatever he wants.

05:12.514 --> 05:14.414
After all,
it's his day, right?

05:14.416 --> 05:16.450
(STONE CLATTERS)
Hey, what was
that small noise?

05:16.452 --> 05:18.418
Let's all go
walk over to it.

05:28.764 --> 05:31.298
<i> Good morning, Agent P.</i>
<i> A quick word.</i>

05:31.300 --> 05:33.367
<i> Recently you've been</i>
<i> having some close calls</i>

05:33.369 --> 05:35.202
<i> and your host family has</i>
<i> almost caught you</i>

05:35.204 --> 05:37.388
<i> sneaking into your</i>
<i> lair several times.</i>

05:37.389 --> 05:39.573
<i> No need to remind you,</i>
<i> but I'll do it anyway,</i>

05:39.575 --> 05:42.042
<i> that if your</i>
<i> cover's blown,</i>

05:42.044 --> 05:44.144
<i> you'll have to be</i>
<i> transferred to another</i>
<i> city</i>
<i> with another host family.</i>

05:44.146 --> 05:46.096
<i> And we both know</i>
<i> you wouldn't like that.</i>

05:46.097 --> 05:48.047
<i> I remember the day</i>
<i> you were first assigned.</i>

05:48.050 --> 05:49.900
Enjoy your platypus!

05:49.901 --> 05:51.751
Thank you, cheerio!

05:51.754 --> 05:53.487
Agent assignment
complete, sir.

05:53.489 --> 05:55.522
Good job, Karl.

05:55.524 --> 05:58.125
If you keep up the great
work,
you'll make unpaid intern
in no time.

05:58.127 --> 05:59.360
KARL: <i> And I did.</i>

05:59.361 --> 06:00.594
<i> Don't get cocky, Karl.</i>

06:00.596 --> 06:03.030
<i> Agent P, as you know,</i>

06:03.031 --> 06:05.465
<i> every operative is</i>
<i> equipped</i>
<i> with an autoscan</i>
<i> replication device</i>

06:05.467 --> 06:07.134
<i> just like the one</i>
<i> in your hat.</i>

06:07.136 --> 06:09.403
<i> We've been using</i>
<i> the information</i>
<i> you've gathered</i>

06:09.404 --> 06:11.671
<i> to replicate</i>
<i> each and every one of</i>
<i> Dr. Doofenshmirtz's</i>
<i> Inators.</i>

06:11.674 --> 06:14.274
<i> Our top men have been</i>
<i> analyzing them to</i>
<i> determine</i>

06:14.276 --> 06:16.710
<i> if they've been</i>
<i> getting smarter</i>
<i> or dumber.</i>

06:16.711 --> 06:19.145
<i> And to be honest,</i>
<i> the jury's still out.</i>

06:19.148 --> 06:20.814
<i> Now we find out that</i>
<i> he's in the process</i>
<i> of building</i>

06:20.816 --> 06:22.816
<i> an</i>
<i> alternate-dimension-related</i>
<i> Inator.</i>

06:22.818 --> 06:25.686
<i> Your assignment</i>
<i> is to stop him before</i>
<i> he finishes building it.</i>

06:25.688 --> 06:27.788
<i> Behind you,</i>
<i> rising dramatically</i>
<i> from the floor,</i>

06:27.790 --> 06:33.193
<i> is Karl,</i>
<i> with some high-tech</i>
<i> gadgets</i>
<i> that you might find</i>

06:33.195 --> 06:36.530
KARL: Uh, sir? Hello?
I didn't step on in time.

06:36.532 --> 06:39.099
Would you mind
lowering the
platform again?

06:39.101 --> 06:44.304
<i> Great. Let me</i>
<i> cue the music again.</i>

06:44.306 --> 06:48.342
Well, obviously,
this first item is our
new wrist
communicationizer.

06:48.344 --> 06:50.777
It has many applications
that will help you
in the field.

06:50.779 --> 06:53.814
For example, a powerful
directional electromagnet.

06:53.816 --> 06:55.782
It will draw
any metal object to you.

06:55.784 --> 06:58.151
See?
And these are aluminum!

06:58.153 --> 07:00.520
<i> Quit goofing around,</i>
<i> Karl,</i>
<i> and show him the</i>
<i> hologram.</i>

07:00.522 --> 07:01.655
Yes, sir.
(MONOGRAM CHUCKLES)

07:01.657 --> 07:03.123
<i> Pretty nifty, huh?</i>

07:03.125 --> 07:04.591
<i> With this device</i>
<i> you'll be able to</i>

07:04.593 --> 07:07.294
<i> contact me</i>
<i> from anywhere</i>
<i> at any time.</i>

07:07.296 --> 07:09.796
<i> But don't call</i>
<i> between 3:30 and 4:00</i>

07:09.798 --> 07:11.832
<i> because that's when</i>
<i> I take a shower.</i>

07:11.834 --> 07:13.533
(EXCLAIMING)

07:13.535 --> 07:15.836
<i> Wait a minute.</i>
<i> Is that me?</i>

07:15.838 --> 07:17.738
Oh, no!

07:17.740 --> 07:20.707
His holographic projection
has become mesmerized
by his video image.

07:20.709 --> 07:22.509
I better shut it off.

07:22.511 --> 07:24.545
And if you
push this button,

07:24.546 --> 07:26.580
it gives your adversary
an incredible ice cream
headache.

07:26.582 --> 07:28.548
(SHOUTING IN PAIN)

07:28.550 --> 07:31.518
It's gone.
You better watch
where you point that!

07:31.520 --> 07:33.520
Hey, girl!
What are you doing?

07:33.522 --> 07:35.822
Stacy, Jeremy's
going to college soon,
and here I am,

07:35.824 --> 07:37.724
concerned with busting
my brothers to my mommy

07:37.726 --> 07:40.394
and living
in this nursery.

07:40.396 --> 07:42.229
A unicorn!
A unicorn, Stacy!

07:42.231 --> 07:44.297
(IN CHILDISH VOICE)
"Hi, I'm six!"

07:44.299 --> 07:45.766
You've gotta help me
get rid of all this junk.

07:45.768 --> 07:47.300
Wow! Bold move!

07:47.302 --> 07:49.870
Yep. Goodbye,
childhood folly,

07:49.872 --> 07:52.673
hello, carefree
undemanding adult life.

07:52.675 --> 07:54.291
Yeah, good luck with that.

07:54.292 --> 07:55.908
Candace, your father and I
are off to the movies.

07:55.911 --> 07:57.611
While we're gone,
you're in charge, okay?

07:57.613 --> 08:00.247
Okay, Mom!

08:00.248 --> 08:02.882
And you know, I'm even
thinking about giving up
on busting my brothers.

08:02.885 --> 08:05.419
The irony is, that as
a grown-up, you don't
need to tell your mom.

08:05.421 --> 08:07.554
You can just
bust them yourself.

08:07.556 --> 08:10.757
(GASPS) That's it!
Stacy, I'm old enough
to bust them myself!

08:10.759 --> 08:12.659
That's what
I just said.

08:12.661 --> 08:16.496
CHORUS:
<i> ♪ Doofenshmirtz</i>
<i> Evil Incorporated! ♪</i>

08:16.498 --> 08:19.566
Now, Perry the Platypus,
quake in terror

08:19.568 --> 08:22.669
as I punch a hole through
to another dimension.

08:22.671 --> 08:25.706
Behold,
the Other-Dimensionator...
NORM: <i> Sir!</i>

08:25.708 --> 08:26.873
What? What?

08:26.875 --> 08:29.159
<i> I finished</i>
<i> setting up the buffet.</i>

08:29.160 --> 08:31.444
For crying out loud, Norm.
I was in the zone!

08:31.447 --> 08:33.313
<i> I just thought</i>
<i> you were playing</i>
<i> with your doll.</i>

08:33.315 --> 08:35.482
It's not a doll,
it's a stand-in!

08:35.484 --> 08:37.551
Pretendy the Practicepus,
see?

08:37.553 --> 08:39.419
I wonder
if Perry the Platypus
practices with a fake me.

08:39.421 --> 08:42.722
It would be nice to know
he cares enough.

08:42.725 --> 08:44.291
PHINEAS:
All systems are green.

08:44.293 --> 08:45.759
Prepare to launch
on my mark.

08:45.761 --> 08:47.594
T minus 30 and counting.

08:47.596 --> 08:51.431
29, 28, 27, 26...

08:51.433 --> 08:53.266
Of course,
you'll only need this

08:53.268 --> 08:55.769
if you're attacked
by one of the royals
or a member of Parliament.

08:55.771 --> 08:58.271
So it's probably okay
to leave the safety on.

08:58.273 --> 09:00.674
And here's your
brand new rocket car.

09:00.676 --> 09:03.510
Sweet, huh?
Good luck, Agent P.

09:03.512 --> 09:06.279
<i> Karl? Did you tell him</i>
<i> the accelerator's</i>
<i> a little touchy?</i>

09:07.549 --> 09:09.015
I think he knows, sir.

09:09.017 --> 09:11.852
PHINEAS: Three, two, one.

09:11.854 --> 09:13.587
Service!

09:18.994 --> 09:20.560
(EXCLAIMING)

09:20.562 --> 09:22.713
Phineas and Ferb,
you are so busted...

09:22.714 --> 09:24.865
Oh, my gosh! Where'd it
go?
You there, small children!

09:24.867 --> 09:27.134
Where's the big
contraption?

09:27.135 --> 09:29.402
I don't know.
It was here
just a moment ago.

09:29.404 --> 09:31.338
It disappeared?

09:31.340 --> 09:32.706
Stacy, do you realize
what this means?
We're done?

09:32.708 --> 09:35.375
No, some kind of
mysterious force

09:35.377 --> 09:38.645
always takes away
Phineas and Ferb's
inventions
before Mom shows up.

09:38.647 --> 09:41.681
This time it took
away their invention
before I showed up!

09:41.683 --> 09:43.817
The mysterious force
recognizes that
I'm now a grown-up.

09:43.819 --> 09:47.320
A mysterious force?
I'm not buying it.

09:47.322 --> 09:49.956
I am a woman of science,
at least that's what
my horoscope said.

09:49.958 --> 09:51.725
Well, I'm going to
prove it to you

09:51.727 --> 09:54.327
and bust my brothers
at the same time!

09:54.329 --> 09:55.562
Where are my brothers?

09:55.564 --> 09:56.897
We just launched them
towards the park.

09:56.899 --> 09:58.565
Buford is there with
the other platypult.

09:58.567 --> 10:01.401
Okay, as the adult,
I decree we are
going to the park.

10:01.403 --> 10:02.736
Does anyone need
to go potty first?

10:05.674 --> 10:06.973
Fine, make it quick.

10:06.975 --> 10:09.943
Ferb, it looks like
we're gonna hit
that building

10:09.945 --> 10:11.878
that looks vaguely
like your head.

10:11.880 --> 10:14.614
Time to give it
a little test.

10:15.984 --> 10:17.884
(MACHINE POWERING DOWN)

10:17.885 --> 10:19.785
Hmm.
Well, I just finished it.
It can't be broken
already.

10:23.058 --> 10:25.525
(SIGHS)
I stand corrected.

10:25.527 --> 10:27.460
All right, what's with
the giant shuttlecock?

10:27.462 --> 10:29.830
We're really sorry, sir.
I don't know what
happened.

10:29.832 --> 10:31.731
One minute,
we were innocently
launching ourselves

10:31.733 --> 10:34.668
across the city in
a badminton platypult.
The next thing we know,

10:34.670 --> 10:36.336
we're bouncing on
up to the eastside

10:36.338 --> 10:37.938
to your deluxe apartment
in the sky.

10:37.940 --> 10:40.807
Well, it looks like
you've totaled my
Other-Dimensionator.

10:40.809 --> 10:43.677
An Other-Dimensionator?
What does it do?

10:43.679 --> 10:46.980
Well, at the moment,
it just stops giant
shuttlecocks, apparently.

10:46.982 --> 10:49.883
But it's supposed
to let me go into
other dimensions.

10:49.885 --> 10:51.551
That's cool!
We can help you fix it.

10:51.553 --> 10:54.654
I'm Phineas,
and this is my
brother Ferb.

10:54.656 --> 10:57.791
I'm Dr. Heinz
Doofenshmirtz,
but my friends call me...
(SIGHS)

11:00.696 --> 11:01.995
I just got in such a funk.

11:01.997 --> 11:04.898
Ferb is naturally
handy with tools.

11:04.900 --> 11:06.132
I bet we could
put this thing back
together in no time.

11:06.134 --> 11:08.902
What the heck.
Before we start,

11:08.904 --> 11:11.321
there's a whole
buffet set up here,
please partake.

11:11.322 --> 11:13.739
I was expecting someone
who seems to be running
late.

11:13.742 --> 11:14.708
You're lucky I got
a rocket car winch.

11:14.710 --> 11:16.877
Lots of guys
don't have that.

11:17.579 --> 11:20.580
PHINEAS: Almost there.

11:20.582 --> 11:23.783
Okay,
field compressor attaches
to the auxiliary
generator.

11:23.785 --> 11:26.019
Was this working before?

11:26.021 --> 11:28.922
Well, if by "working"
you mean "functioning
properly," then no.

11:28.924 --> 11:30.741
Well, I think
I see your problem.

11:30.742 --> 11:32.559
Everything's wired through
this self-destruct button.

11:32.561 --> 11:34.027
Do you even need that?

11:34.029 --> 11:36.396
Well, of course I...

11:36.398 --> 11:39.432
Wait a minute.
No, I do not need that.

11:39.434 --> 11:41.635
You are absolutely right.

11:41.637 --> 11:43.904
So Ferb has rigged up
this remote control

11:43.906 --> 11:45.639
so that if we get
separated from the portal,
we can open another one.

11:45.641 --> 11:46.806
Nice touch, kid.

11:46.808 --> 11:49.009
I guess this is
the last piece.

11:49.011 --> 11:50.710
Okay, Ferb,
boost me up.

11:54.149 --> 11:54.781
Ooh, I cannot wait!

11:58.520 --> 12:00.504
(CHATTERING)

12:00.505 --> 12:02.489
PHINEAS:
There you are, Perry.
Perry?

12:02.491 --> 12:04.891
Yeah. He's our
pet platypus.

12:04.893 --> 12:05.692
Is every platypus
named Perry?

12:05.694 --> 12:08.561
In a perfect world, yes.

12:08.563 --> 12:09.963
Well, he's a cute
little fellow.

12:09.965 --> 12:11.665
Hi, there.
Coochee, coochee...
Ow! Ow! Ow!

12:11.667 --> 12:13.934
Perry, no!
We do not bite
the elderly.

12:13.936 --> 12:16.036
Again, ow!
It's okay.

12:16.038 --> 12:17.804
Platypuses don't
typically like me.

12:17.805 --> 12:19.571
Well, Perry, you're just
in time to see us open
a window

12:19.574 --> 12:22.542
into another dimension.

12:22.544 --> 12:24.210
Perry, no!
What are you doing?

12:24.212 --> 12:25.946
No, no!

12:25.948 --> 12:28.581
Perry, this is not
tug of war!

12:28.583 --> 12:30.483
This is not
tug of war!

12:30.485 --> 12:32.686
Silly boy,
what's gotten into him?

12:32.688 --> 12:33.887
All right,
let's get this show
on the road, huh?

12:33.889 --> 12:36.656
<i> Remember,</i>
<i> if your cover is blown,</i>

12:36.658 --> 12:39.025
<i> you'll never see</i>
<i> the boys again.</i>

12:39.027 --> 12:40.593
Hey, does anyone hear
someone talking?

12:40.595 --> 12:42.796
<i> Never see them again.</i>

12:42.798 --> 12:46.900
Okay, here we go.
Right in...

12:49.137 --> 12:51.104
Perry! No!
Not on the sofa!

12:51.106 --> 12:54.741
I'm sorry, Dr. D.
We should take him out.

12:54.743 --> 12:56.760
No, no. Wait.
It'll be all right.

12:56.761 --> 12:58.778
I was planning on
replacing this
old couch anyway.

12:58.780 --> 13:00.680
Now come on.
Let's light
this pop stand,

13:00.682 --> 13:00.880
or however it goes.

13:05.887 --> 13:07.754
Gosh, this is...
It's kind of
weird, actually.

13:07.756 --> 13:10.123
I'm usually thwarted
by this point.

13:10.125 --> 13:12.025
Well, I guess
he's not coming.

13:12.027 --> 13:15.195
And now, behold!

13:15.197 --> 13:19.899
The mind-blowing
first images from beyond
our dimensional reality!

13:27.876 --> 13:29.142
Hmm.

13:29.144 --> 13:32.078
It's a...
It's a couch.

13:32.080 --> 13:34.080
That's a bit
anticlimactic.

13:34.082 --> 13:37.984
I guess it's a nice couch,
though...

13:37.986 --> 13:41.121
Hey! I got an idea!
Let's swap my couch
for that one!

13:42.524 --> 13:44.374
Um...

13:44.375 --> 13:46.225
I got it. I got...
Or maybe I...

13:46.228 --> 13:48.228
Come on, you want to
give me a hand here?

13:48.230 --> 13:49.596
Whoa! Awesome,
check it out.

13:49.598 --> 13:50.764
(MAN CLEARS THROAT)

13:53.101 --> 13:53.833
(STUTTERS) Hello.

13:56.038 --> 13:57.637
Say, aren't you...

13:57.639 --> 13:58.905
PHINEAS: Hey, Dr. D!
Look at this.

13:58.907 --> 14:00.273
Hold that thought.

14:00.274 --> 14:01.640
You're famous here.

14:12.687 --> 14:14.120
DOOFENSHMIRTZ'S VOICE:
<i> Get off!</i>

14:16.291 --> 14:19.692
(IN DISBELIEF)
"Heinz Doofenshmirtz,
your leader"?

14:24.733 --> 14:27.934
A whole tri-state area
where I am already in
charge!

14:27.936 --> 14:30.770
Yeah! Hold on,
I gotta go check
something out.

14:30.772 --> 14:33.773
Uh, yoo-hoo!
Hello, again.

14:33.775 --> 14:36.643
Is this some kind of test?
Is that really you, sir?

14:36.645 --> 14:38.244
(LAUGHS) Holy boy!

14:38.246 --> 14:42.682
Even the great
Francis Monogram's
my slave in this
dimension!

14:42.684 --> 14:44.217
I prefer the term
"indentured
executive assistant."

14:44.219 --> 14:46.352
Well, I want to meet
this other dimension me.

14:46.354 --> 14:48.755
Where can I find him?

14:48.757 --> 14:50.323
Oh. You're from
another dimension?

14:50.325 --> 14:52.258
Well, he'll probably
wanna see you then.

14:52.260 --> 14:53.993
He's into that
freaky sort of stuff.

14:53.995 --> 14:56.996
Have a seat
and I'll let him know
you're on your way up.

14:56.998 --> 14:59.365
Okay. So I just
gotta sit here and...

15:02.003 --> 15:04.337
CHORUS:
<i> ♪ He's Doof Doof</i>
<i> Doof Doof Doof Doof Doof</i>

15:04.339 --> 15:06.339
<i> ♪ Bask in his glory</i>
<i> Kneel at his feet</i>

15:06.341 --> 15:08.842
<i> ♪ You're in for such a</i>
<i> treat</i>
<i> He's Doofenshmirtz ♪</i>

15:08.844 --> 15:10.743
That was awesome!

15:10.745 --> 15:13.179
All right, who's
interrupting my...

15:13.181 --> 15:14.681
Hmm.

15:16.351 --> 15:16.816
Hmm.

15:21.923 --> 15:23.089
Do I know you?

15:23.091 --> 15:25.391
Yeah! I'm you from
another dimension!

15:25.393 --> 15:28.194
Well, that would explain
the handsomeness.

15:28.196 --> 15:30.213
Right back at you,
big guy.

15:30.214 --> 15:32.231
Does that mean
you and I are
exactly alike?

15:32.234 --> 15:34.868
I suppose so.

15:34.870 --> 15:37.103
<i> ♪ Do you want</i>
<i> some rice pudding?</i>

15:37.105 --> 15:38.705
<i> ♪ Ick, no, that's gross</i>

15:38.707 --> 15:40.740
<i> ♪ It was a test</i>
<i> Almond brittle?</i>

15:40.742 --> 15:43.143
<i> ♪ Oh, I love it the most</i>
<i> ♪ Me, too</i>

15:43.145 --> 15:44.711
<i> ♪ Do you collect coins?</i>

15:44.713 --> 15:47.080
<i> ♪ Yeah, just in case</i>

15:47.082 --> 15:50.817
<i> ♪ Vending machines become</i>
<i> the dominant race</i>

15:50.819 --> 15:54.721
<i> ♪ I've been alone</i>
<i> all these years</i>

15:54.723 --> 15:56.756
<i> ♪ With my irrational</i>
<i> fears</i>

15:56.758 --> 15:58.758
But not the
vending machine thing.
That's gonna happen.

15:58.760 --> 16:01.294
<i> ♪ But now before me, I</i>
<i> see</i>

16:02.697 --> 16:04.931
<i> ♪ Someone with whom I</i>
<i> agree</i>

16:04.933 --> 16:08.968
<i> ♪ I've found</i>
<i> a brand new best friend</i>
<i> And it's me</i>

16:08.970 --> 16:11.804
<i> ♪ I've found</i>
<i> a brand new best friend</i>
<i> And it's me</i>

16:19.981 --> 16:21.948
<i> ♪ I thought I'd be taller</i>

16:21.950 --> 16:23.783
<i> ♪ I've been told I slouch</i>

16:23.785 --> 16:26.219
<i> ♪ I thought</i>
<i> I'd have both my eyes</i>
<i> You know</i>

16:26.221 --> 16:27.787
<i> ♪ It's in this pouch</i>

16:27.789 --> 16:29.923
Ouch! You know,
I can't help but notice

16:29.925 --> 16:32.292
that your scar goes
over your eye patch.

16:32.294 --> 16:33.693
Yeah?

16:34.329 --> 16:34.861
Nothing.

16:36.831 --> 16:38.831
<i> ♪ Do llamas weird you</i>
<i> out?</i>

16:38.833 --> 16:40.433
<i> ♪ Yeah, are they camels</i>
<i> or sheep?</i>

16:40.435 --> 16:42.435
<i> ♪ No, no, I meant Lorenzo</i>

16:42.437 --> 16:44.337
<i> ♪ That's right</i>
<i> He played Meap</i>

16:44.339 --> 16:45.905
<i> ♪ Now I know all about</i>
<i> you</i>

16:48.343 --> 16:51.177
<i> ♪ And you know</i>
<i> all about me</i>

16:51.179 --> 16:52.312
<i> ♪ Oh-wee-ooh!</i>

16:52.314 --> 16:56.216
<i> ♪ And now before me I see</i>

16:56.218 --> 16:58.818
<i> ♪ Someone with whom I</i>
<i> agree</i>

16:58.820 --> 17:02.722
<i> ♪ I've found</i>
<i> a brand new best friend</i>
<i> And it's me</i>

17:02.724 --> 17:06.459
<i> ♪ I've found</i>
<i> a brand new best friend</i>
<i> And it's me</i>

17:06.461 --> 17:09.194
<i> ♪ Now that I found you</i>

17:09.464 --> 17:13.366
<i> ♪ We can be a duo</i>

17:13.367 --> 17:15.001
<i> ♪ That's right</i>

17:15.002 --> 17:18.805
<i> ♪ Twice the evil</i>
<i> Double Doofenshmirtz</i>

17:18.807 --> 17:22.141
<i> ♪ Coming at you Fridays ♪</i>

17:22.143 --> 17:24.377
What's that?
I mean, are we doing
a TV show together?

17:24.378 --> 17:26.378
No. It just sort of
sounded like...

17:26.381 --> 17:28.314
I mean, we could.
We should!

17:28.316 --> 17:31.017
Hmm. Maybe we're
not so much alike.

17:31.019 --> 17:32.385
That can be
our catch phrase.

17:32.387 --> 17:34.354
You're the grumpy one.

17:37.158 --> 17:39.892
Wow, he's done
really well for himself.
What do you think, Perry?

17:45.133 --> 17:46.432
(CHATTERING)

17:46.434 --> 17:49.002
Hey, where is Dr. D?

17:49.004 --> 17:52.105
So what you're telling me
is you're still not ruler
of your tri-state area?

17:52.107 --> 17:54.240
Well, obviously you
did not have to deal

17:54.242 --> 17:55.375
with my nemesis,
Perry the Platypus.

17:55.377 --> 17:57.944
Oh, didn't I? Observe.

17:59.381 --> 18:00.513
What is it?

18:03.551 --> 18:06.919
DOOFENSHMIRTZ 2D:
This is Perry the
Platyborg!

18:06.921 --> 18:11.257
He was once my nemesis,
but now, he's general
of my army!

18:11.259 --> 18:13.259
Wow! You are good!

18:13.261 --> 18:14.861
DOOFENSHMIRTZ 2D:
Dismissed.

18:15.930 --> 18:17.897
That was awesome!

18:17.899 --> 18:19.716
Now who's
interrupting me?

18:19.717 --> 18:21.534
Remind me to berate
my indentured
executive assistant.

18:21.536 --> 18:22.869
No, man, it's cool.
They're with me.

18:22.871 --> 18:25.972
Hey, Dr. D.
We thought we'd lost you.

18:25.974 --> 18:27.206
Hi, fellas!

18:27.208 --> 18:29.876
You dare to bring
a secret agent in here?

18:29.878 --> 18:31.177
This boy's
a secret agent?

18:31.179 --> 18:33.379
No, not him!
The quiet one?

18:33.381 --> 18:34.914
DOOFENSHMIRTZ 2D:
No! Not... No. Him!

18:34.916 --> 18:37.283
This plant?

18:37.285 --> 18:40.887
The platypus!
That's Secret Agent
Perry the Platypus!

18:40.889 --> 18:43.156
Oh, hey.
He's just a platypus.
He doesn't do much.

18:43.158 --> 18:46.192
This is rich.
I see what's
going on here.

18:46.194 --> 18:49.362
You really think
that he's your pet,
don't you?

18:49.364 --> 18:51.097
Wrong! He's using you!

18:51.099 --> 18:52.598
You're just his cover.
He's a secret agent!

18:52.600 --> 18:55.034
Here, here,
let me prove it.

18:55.036 --> 18:57.603
General Platyborg,
come down here at once.

18:57.605 --> 19:00.606
He'll be here
in just a second.
Ow! Ow! Ow!

19:00.608 --> 19:02.608
All right, Platyborg,
you see that platypus?

19:02.610 --> 19:03.843
You know what to do.

19:04.212 --> 19:05.945
Perry!

19:08.850 --> 19:10.383
What was that for?
Perry, are you okay?

19:10.385 --> 19:12.618
Told you.

19:12.620 --> 19:14.620
How are his vitals?

19:14.622 --> 19:18.124
Wait, let me
try something.
Platyborg!

19:18.126 --> 19:19.625
Do the same thing
to those two boys.
What?

19:21.863 --> 19:22.628
What?

19:24.132 --> 19:26.999
CHORUS:
<i> ♪ Perry ♪</i>

19:27.869 --> 19:29.635
Perry?

19:29.637 --> 19:31.571
Yes! I knew it!

19:31.573 --> 19:33.172
Wait a minute.
I'm confused.

19:33.174 --> 19:33.940
Why does their platypus
fight so good?

19:37.045 --> 19:37.877
Perry the Platypus!

19:39.280 --> 19:40.646
Really?

19:40.648 --> 19:41.647
What?

19:42.350 --> 19:43.483
Perry?

19:43.485 --> 19:44.650
Get them!

19:48.123 --> 19:49.555
You're a secret agent?

19:50.558 --> 19:51.891
Whoa! Whoa!

19:54.195 --> 19:56.262
Hey, be careful with that.

19:56.264 --> 19:58.297
So this is where
you disappear to
every day?

19:58.299 --> 20:00.199
You come here
and fight this guy?

20:00.201 --> 20:03.369
No, he fights me.
He doesn't really
know this guy.

20:03.371 --> 20:05.171
You fight a pharmacist?
Why would you even do
that?

20:05.173 --> 20:07.640
Actually,
I'm an evil scientist.

20:07.642 --> 20:10.476
A lot of people
are confused by
the lab coat.

20:10.478 --> 20:12.111
You're evil?
He's evil?

20:12.280 --> 20:14.547
(GLASS CRACKING)

20:17.652 --> 20:20.353
So, not only have you
been leading a double
life this whole time,

20:20.355 --> 20:23.222
but you sat there
and let us help
an evil scientist

20:23.224 --> 20:24.690
open an evil portal
into an evil dimension!

20:24.692 --> 20:26.659
And you did nothing
to stop us?

20:26.661 --> 20:29.128
Well, he did pee
on the couch.

20:29.130 --> 20:30.963
Wait a second,
I just realized.

20:30.965 --> 20:34.100
That was a conscious
choice.
You peed on my couch!

20:34.102 --> 20:35.635
No, no.
That wasn't enough.

20:35.637 --> 20:37.503
That's when you should
have
put on your little hat.

20:37.505 --> 20:40.506
Not now, after we've
gone through it into
this mess!

20:40.508 --> 20:43.376
For badness sake,
you can hash all
this out in prison.

20:43.378 --> 20:45.144
Guards!

20:45.146 --> 20:46.579
Ow! Brain freeze!

20:47.515 --> 20:49.182
(YELLING)

20:55.290 --> 20:59.225
I'm sorry.
I'm just having trouble
processing this right now.

20:59.227 --> 21:01.327
"So you've discovered
your pet is a secret
agent."

21:01.329 --> 21:02.528
I don't want
your pamphlet!

21:04.699 --> 21:05.965
Uh-oh.

21:10.171 --> 21:13.005
He's coming
back around!

21:19.547 --> 21:21.047
(GRUNTING)

21:24.018 --> 21:26.052
You have got
to be kidding me.

21:27.355 --> 21:30.323
For crying out loud.

21:30.325 --> 21:31.991
What, they didn't teach
you
how to get out of this
in spy school?

21:40.201 --> 21:42.435
Oh, snap.

21:42.437 --> 21:43.503
Look! There's a logo
on this parachute!

21:43.505 --> 21:45.638
He's got his own logo?

22:06.060 --> 22:08.461
All this time we're like,
"He's a platypus.
He doesn't do much."

22:08.463 --> 22:11.764
Well, apparently you do!
You do... You're...

22:11.766 --> 22:13.633
You're tangled up in
the...
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

22:25.780 --> 22:29.315
Wow! Saved by
unconventional
architecture.

22:29.317 --> 22:29.782
<i> May I please</i>
<i> see your papers?</i>

22:34.188 --> 22:36.188
<i> Show me your papers</i>
<i> or be destroyed.</i>

23:01.115 --> 23:04.317
Curse you,
Perry the Platypus!

23:04.319 --> 23:06.218
Jinx! You owe me a soda.

23:07.622 --> 23:09.689
<i> Get me! I'm a Georgia</i>
<i> O'Keeffe painting!</i>

23:11.726 --> 23:13.492
Fourth and Main.

23:16.798 --> 23:19.365
What? No tip?

23:19.367 --> 23:21.167
Never mind. I'm good.

23:29.314 --> 23:32.048
Looks like
they're gone.

23:32.451 --> 23:33.851
You're a secret agent?

23:33.853 --> 23:35.586
And you've been
living with us
this whole time?

23:35.588 --> 23:37.087
Was that evil guy right?

23:37.089 --> 23:38.923
Were we just
a cover story to you?

23:38.925 --> 23:41.325
I mean, were you ever
really our pet
or part of our family?

23:41.327 --> 23:44.395
Well, apparently not,
'cause you didn't trust us
enough to tell us.

23:44.397 --> 23:47.331
Anyone else
around here leading
a bizarre double life?

23:47.333 --> 23:50.067
Put your hand down, Ferb.

23:52.104 --> 23:54.738
You're a secret agent!
He's a secret agent!

23:56.943 --> 23:59.043
You're right, Ferb.
We've got to concentrate
on the task at hand.

23:59.045 --> 24:01.779
We've got to get back
to our dimension,

24:01.781 --> 24:03.514
and I don't even know
where to start!

24:03.516 --> 24:05.516
That's right!
The remote!

24:05.518 --> 24:06.784
I knew that would
come in handy.

24:06.786 --> 24:07.785
All right,
let's go home.

24:09.822 --> 24:11.922
Wait, that's not
our dimension.

24:12.959 --> 24:13.624
Nope. Uh-uh.

24:17.630 --> 24:20.564
Now this thing's broken.
We're gonna need some
help.

24:20.566 --> 24:22.900
I know!
Let's go find us!

24:26.138 --> 24:29.073
Wait, I just realized,

24:29.075 --> 24:32.776
you could have been
cleaning your own
litter box this whole
time!

24:32.778 --> 24:37.114
We are not done
with this conversation.

24:37.116 --> 24:40.417
So tell me,
other dimension me,
what do you see here?

24:40.419 --> 24:41.819
An ordinary platypus.

24:41.821 --> 24:43.520
And now
what do you see?

24:43.522 --> 24:45.122
Perry the Platypus!

24:45.124 --> 24:46.790
You know,
I'm starting to see

24:46.792 --> 24:49.159
why you haven't
become ruler
in your dimension.

24:49.161 --> 24:51.829
All right,
Mr. Eviler-Than-Thou,

24:51.830 --> 24:54.498
just how did you
manage to take over
the tri-state area anyway?

24:54.500 --> 24:58.035
Simple, I used
an army of big,
scary robots.

24:58.037 --> 25:00.471
NORMBOTS: <i> We should</i>
<i> do lunch sometime.</i>

25:00.473 --> 25:02.907
Wow, that is scary.

25:02.909 --> 25:04.808
I tried that
robot thing once, too.

25:04.810 --> 25:06.577
I hid the self-destruct
button
on the bottoms of their
feet

25:06.579 --> 25:08.545
<i> so no one</i>
<i> could reach them.</i>

25:12.184 --> 25:13.384
And march!

25:13.385 --> 25:14.585
I think I've said enough.
I still don't get it.

25:14.587 --> 25:17.922
If we're the same person,
why are you so much better
at being evil than me?

25:17.924 --> 25:21.959
True evil is born
through pain and loss.

25:21.961 --> 25:25.162
You see,
when I was a small boy
back in Gimelschtump,

25:25.164 --> 25:27.998
I had a toy train.

25:28.000 --> 25:29.566
<i> Then, one day I lost it.</i>

25:29.568 --> 25:30.834
Choo-Choo?

25:34.674 --> 25:37.141
That's... That's it?
What do you mean?

25:37.143 --> 25:39.043
That's your emotionally
scarring back-story?

25:39.045 --> 25:41.011
That's your
great tragedy?

25:41.013 --> 25:43.747
Dude! I was
raised by ocelots.
I mean, literally.

25:43.749 --> 25:46.116
Disowned by my parents
and raised by
Central American wildcats,

25:46.118 --> 25:48.485
and you're telling me
you lost a toy train?
That's all?

25:48.487 --> 25:50.688
That's all you got,
really?

