these things.

33:41.109 --> 33:43.093
Hey! It's Buford.
Who are you guys?

33:43.095 --> 33:45.529
We're Candace's brothers.
We're going to Isabella's.

33:45.531 --> 33:47.130
Are you part of
the Resistance?

33:47.132 --> 33:49.199
I used to be
in the Resistance,

33:49.201 --> 33:52.135
but I got so good
at it that I started
resisting them.

33:52.137 --> 33:54.504
DOOFENSHMIRTZ: Behold,
the Other-Dimensionator!

33:54.506 --> 33:56.706
Actually, this is the
other
Other-Dimensionator.

33:56.708 --> 34:00.444
The Other-Dimensionator is
back in the other
dimension.

34:00.446 --> 34:03.079
Okay, step one is,
push this button.

34:03.081 --> 34:05.715
Step two,
stand back in awe!

34:07.986 --> 34:09.753
(MACHINE POWERING DOWN)

34:09.754 --> 34:11.521
(GROANS)
That's it?

34:11.523 --> 34:13.523
Now that
I think about it,

34:13.525 --> 34:16.493
those two boys made some
modifications to my design

34:16.495 --> 34:19.161
which may have
allowed it to...
You know...

34:19.164 --> 34:20.746
To work.

34:20.748 --> 34:22.331
Great, now I need
those two boys?

34:25.237 --> 34:27.637
Ah! Perry the Platypus!

34:27.639 --> 34:31.241
Jinx!
You owe me two sodas!

34:31.243 --> 34:33.109
Listen, Perry the
Platypus,
I know I told you

34:33.110 --> 34:35.212
if you turned yourself in
I wouldn't hurt your
friends,

34:35.214 --> 34:37.246
but change of plans!

34:37.248 --> 34:40.083
Now I need to hunt
them down which might
involve a little hurting.

34:40.085 --> 34:43.053
I know that makes me
a liar, but hello! Evil!

34:44.623 --> 34:47.056
Come on,
Isabella's house
is right through...

34:54.166 --> 34:54.731
What you doing?

34:54.733 --> 34:57.767
Isabella?

34:57.769 --> 35:00.737
Do I know you?
Hey, Isabella!

35:00.739 --> 35:03.306
Him I know.
Buford, what do you want?

35:03.308 --> 35:05.108
I thought you were
resisting us?

35:05.110 --> 35:07.010
I was helping
Candace's brothers
cross the street.

35:07.012 --> 35:09.379
Candace has two sets
of twin brothers?

35:09.381 --> 35:12.148
No, he and I are
from another dimension.

35:12.150 --> 35:13.450
We're trying
to get back.

35:13.452 --> 35:14.584
All right, girls,
release them.

35:20.459 --> 35:22.192
Why would you want to come
to this dimension, anyway?

35:22.194 --> 35:24.060
Well, we didn't mean
to come here.

35:24.062 --> 35:26.630
Now we can't get back
unless we can fix
this device.

35:26.631 --> 35:29.199
Well, we may have
someone who can
help you. Dr. Baljeet.

35:29.201 --> 35:30.267
Baljeet!

35:30.269 --> 35:32.536
That's Dr. Baljeet to you!

35:32.538 --> 35:34.704
Were you not listening?
Here is the crux
of your problem.

35:34.706 --> 35:37.707
Think of the universe
and all of the many
dimensions as circular.

35:37.709 --> 35:40.076
The energy flows
between the dimensions
like this, clockwise.

35:40.078 --> 35:44.481
Say this is your dimension
and this is our dimension.

35:44.483 --> 35:46.349
You traveled with
the flow of energy.

35:46.351 --> 35:48.285
So going clockwise
would be easy!

35:48.287 --> 35:51.555
Going counter clockwise
would take 8 million
gigawatts of energy,

35:51.557 --> 35:54.190
overloading
the local power grid.

35:54.192 --> 35:56.092
I have prepared
a little song to help
illustrate my point.

35:56.094 --> 35:58.061
<i> ♪ If you travel</i>
<i> through dimensions</i>

35:58.063 --> 36:01.197
<i> ♪ Going clockwise</i>
<i> makes it easy</i>

36:01.199 --> 36:03.166
<i> ♪ Going counter clockwise</i>
<i> would take 8 million</i>
<i> gigawatts of energy</i>

36:03.168 --> 36:07.070
<i> ♪ overloading</i>
<i> the local power grid ♪</i>

36:08.173 --> 36:09.773
I know,
it needs a chorus.

36:09.775 --> 36:12.025
Anyway, without the
8 million gigawatts,

36:12.026 --> 36:14.276
you would have
to go clockwise,
the long way around.

36:14.279 --> 36:16.179
Theoretically,
you would get home
but there is no telling

36:16.181 --> 36:18.114
how many dimensions
you would have to
go through.

36:18.116 --> 36:20.183
Well, do you think
you can help us
get enough power

36:20.185 --> 36:21.952
to open the window
backwards
so we can get home?

36:21.953 --> 36:23.720
Well, we should probably
ask our leader.

36:23.722 --> 36:25.655
(IN DEEP VOICE)
Ask your leader what?

36:25.657 --> 36:27.290
(COUGHING)

36:27.292 --> 36:30.126
Who made the topiary
out of wild parsnips?

36:30.128 --> 36:31.795
I'm allergic,
and it's messing up
my voice.

36:31.797 --> 36:34.264
Candace, you're the leader
of the resistance?

36:34.266 --> 36:37.167
What are you two
(IN NORMAL VOICE)
doing here?

36:37.169 --> 36:39.569
Never mind,
I'll deal with you later.
You two,

36:39.571 --> 36:42.172
I've been spending
all these years trying
to keep my brothers safe

36:42.174 --> 36:44.641
and suddenly their faces
are
all over the Doofen
Channel.

36:44.643 --> 36:45.809
We're just trying
to get home.

36:45.811 --> 36:47.444
Well, what's stopping you?

36:47.446 --> 36:50.146
Right now?
Quantum physics.
Baljeet.

36:50.148 --> 36:51.815
We need to generate
8 million gigawatts

36:51.817 --> 36:53.406
for inter-dimensional
travel.

36:53.407 --> 36:54.996
Then we've got
work to do.

36:54.997 --> 36:56.586
Isabella, start
redirecting the power.
Aye aye!

36:56.588 --> 36:58.321
Gretchen! Monitor
the Doofen Channel.

36:58.323 --> 36:59.840
Make sure we're not
raising any alarms.

36:59.841 --> 37:01.358
I'm on it.
Buford, keep resisting.

37:01.360 --> 37:03.777
No!
Excellent.

37:03.778 --> 37:06.195
(IN DEEP VOICE)
And will somebody
get rid of that topiary!

37:06.198 --> 37:07.397
