38:00.886 --> 38:02.519
<i> Now go to bed!</i>

38:02.521 --> 38:03.953
We've got to save him!
Oh, no.

38:03.955 --> 38:05.872
Too risky.
You've got to get back
to your dimension.

38:05.873 --> 38:07.790
We're not going anywhere
without our platypus.

38:07.793 --> 38:09.959
I thought you told us
he was just using you
as a cover.

38:09.961 --> 38:11.628
I know what I said.
I was hurt.

38:11.630 --> 38:13.196
But even if
it was all an act,

38:13.198 --> 38:14.498
he's still
a part of the family,

38:14.499 --> 38:15.799
and we're not
leaving him behind.

38:15.801 --> 38:17.784
I may never be able
to open this again.

38:17.785 --> 38:19.768
It doesn't matter.
We're going back for him.

38:19.771 --> 38:21.438
Well, then
you're on your own.
Fine.

38:21.440 --> 38:23.440
Just tell us where
Doofenshmirtz keeps
his prisoners.

38:23.442 --> 38:25.308
We have to help them!
No, we don't.

38:25.310 --> 38:28.678
Yes, we do. Remember
how we felt when our
Perry disappeared?

38:32.584 --> 38:34.451
Oh, criminy,
I must be crazy.

38:34.453 --> 38:35.585
All right,
we can get there
through the tunnels.

38:35.587 --> 38:37.954
Yes!
Let's suit up, people!

38:37.956 --> 38:39.756
You know what, Stacy?

38:39.758 --> 38:41.424
I'm tired of
the mysterious force
pushing me around.

38:41.426 --> 38:43.593
I'm going to show it
who's boss.
Candace, wait!

38:43.595 --> 38:44.728
I will try to keep it open
for as long as possible

38:44.730 --> 38:47.464
but the window
is very unstable.

38:47.466 --> 38:49.365
Even the slightest
disturbance will
cause it to collapse.

38:53.305 --> 38:55.438
Like that, for instance.
Hey, Candace.

38:55.440 --> 38:58.308
You guys are so...
Wait, why are there
four of you?

38:58.310 --> 38:59.809
Oh, these guys are
from this dimension.

38:59.811 --> 39:01.177
Are we inside
the mysterious force?

39:01.178 --> 39:02.544
I'm not sure
I understand
the question.

39:02.547 --> 39:05.281
And why is Isabella
suddenly fashionable?

39:05.283 --> 39:06.549
What do you mean,
"suddenly"?

39:06.550 --> 39:07.816
Seriously,
where are we?

39:07.819 --> 39:10.320
Candace, I'm sure you have
a million questions,

39:10.322 --> 39:11.855
but right now we have
to save Perry from being
turned into a cyborg.

39:11.857 --> 39:13.323
What?
We'll explain on the way.

39:13.325 --> 39:14.691
So, how do I dress
in your dimension?

39:14.693 --> 39:17.427
Hey, is that me?
I look good!

39:17.429 --> 39:19.262
Oh, no.
You two stay here.

39:19.264 --> 39:20.897
But we want to help.
That's an order!

39:25.837 --> 39:28.805
CANDACE: Wait,
so in this dimension,
Perry is a secret agent?

39:28.807 --> 39:30.907
No, in this dimension
he's a cyborg.

39:30.909 --> 39:32.709
So, where is he an agent?

39:32.711 --> 39:34.477
That would be
in our dimension.

39:34.479 --> 39:35.678
But we're not in
our dimension now.

39:35.680 --> 39:38.882
Okay, I'm having trouble
processing this.

39:38.884 --> 39:40.550
Now I wish
I hadn't thrown away
that pamphlet.

39:41.686 --> 39:43.603
And why are we
in mine cars?

39:43.604 --> 39:45.521
This'll take us as far
as the underground
entrance

39:45.524 --> 39:47.124
to Doof's headquarters.

39:47.125 --> 39:48.725
From there we go up
the ventilation shaft.

39:48.727 --> 39:50.627
The detainment center
is on level four.

39:50.629 --> 39:52.061
And the snack bar's
on level five!

39:52.063 --> 39:53.997
If there's time.

39:53.999 --> 39:56.566
Buford.

39:56.568 --> 39:58.067
I'm just gonna
get some nachos.

40:05.610 --> 40:08.645
So, if there's another me
and another them,

40:08.647 --> 40:11.981
then there must also be
a Jeremy Johnson here,
too, right?

40:11.983 --> 40:14.384
Huh? Oh, yeah,
Johnson, Jeremy.

40:14.386 --> 40:16.820
Leads a three-man strike
team on the north side.
Good soldier.

40:16.822 --> 40:19.673
Good soldier?
That's all you
think of him?

40:19.674 --> 40:22.525
Don't you think
he's dreamy or cool
or even cute?

40:22.527 --> 40:23.793
Tell me at least
you think he's cute.

40:25.497 --> 40:26.896
Cute doesn't win
the war, kid.

40:27.799 --> 40:30.466
Oh. Well, I guess.

40:30.468 --> 40:33.369
But what do you guys
do around here for,
you know, fun?

40:33.371 --> 40:35.071
Look, "Candace" is it?

40:35.073 --> 40:37.874
No offense, but fun
isn't really on my agenda.

40:37.876 --> 40:39.976
You know, since
Doofenshmirtz
took over the tri-state
area,

40:39.978 --> 40:41.978
even though
I was a little girl,

40:41.980 --> 40:43.546
I've been focused
on one thing
and one thing only.

40:43.548 --> 40:45.348
He's going down,
down, down.

40:45.350 --> 40:46.716
Down, down, down, I know.

40:46.718 --> 40:48.518
But what about BFF's?
Or slumber parties?

40:48.520 --> 40:50.119
Or busting your
little brothers?

40:50.121 --> 40:52.822
Busting my brothers?

40:52.824 --> 40:55.525
I spent every day
of my life trying to
protect my little
brothers.

40:55.527 --> 40:56.860
I had to grow up
pretty quick around here

40:56.862 --> 40:58.494
to make sure
they didn't have to.

40:58.496 --> 41:00.797
Gee, you make growing up
sound like it's a bad
thing.

41:00.799 --> 41:04.400
It is what it is.
I'll do whatever it takes
to protect the ones I
love.

41:04.402 --> 41:05.935
Aw! Thanks, sis!

41:05.937 --> 41:07.437
What are you guys
doing here?

41:07.438 --> 41:08.938
We're here to help.
Sir, we're nearing
the target!

41:08.940 --> 41:11.107
Don't move!

41:16.448 --> 41:19.148
Okay, people,
change of plans.

41:19.150 --> 41:20.850
This is as far as we go.

41:20.851 --> 41:22.551
We're not going
to help them?

41:22.554 --> 41:24.638
No, we're gonna
get you two home
where it's safe.

41:24.639 --> 41:26.723
But we wanna...
Look, this isn't our
fight.

41:26.725 --> 41:31.394
It's their fight,
and you two shouldn't
have gotten involved.

41:31.396 --> 41:32.495
Maybe none of us should
have.
Now we're out of here.

41:36.067 --> 41:38.768
I don't remember it being
so dark down here.

41:38.770 --> 41:40.570
Dark?
That's because it's a
trap!

41:40.572 --> 41:43.106
And if it was light,
you would have
seen us and run away,

41:43.108 --> 41:45.475
hence ruining the trap!

41:45.477 --> 41:46.776
I think they get that.

41:46.778 --> 41:48.778
PHINEAS: Perry!

41:48.780 --> 41:51.981
We, uh... We, well,
came to rescue you.

41:54.391 --> 41:56.057
So far it's not going
as well as we'd hoped.

41:56.327 --> 41:57.826
We didn't have
a lot of time to,

41:57.828 --> 41:59.361
you know, plan
something elaborate,

41:59.363 --> 42:01.763
but I guess
we could have created
some sort of diversion

42:01.765 --> 42:03.632
just in case...

42:03.634 --> 42:06.668
(SIGHS)
Yeah, we could have
thought this out more.

42:06.670 --> 42:10.839
(LAUGHS) I got you
and I got your
little friends, too!

42:10.841 --> 42:14.109
Game over! You lose!
I win!

42:14.111 --> 42:17.346
Mark this the hour
of your doom,
Perry the Platypus.

42:18.082 --> 42:20.315
Three forty...

42:20.317 --> 42:22.818
I got one of these
watches with just
the little hash marks.

42:22.820 --> 42:24.820
It doesn't even have
the numbers on it.

42:24.822 --> 42:26.755
Let's just say
it's between
3:30 and 4:00,

42:26.757 --> 42:27.055
Eastern Standard Time.

42:30.694 --> 42:31.760
Whoa!
(SCREAMS)

42:35.366 --> 42:38.734
<i> I told you,</i>
<i> not between</i>
<i> 3:30 and 4:00!</i>

42:42.973 --> 42:44.556
They're getting away!

42:44.557 --> 42:46.140
(ALARM BLARING)

42:46.143 --> 42:48.143
I knew this was
a bad idea. All right,
everyone in the cars!

42:49.246 --> 42:52.714
Go, go, go, go, go!
Isabella, start the motor!

42:52.716 --> 42:54.783
Yes, sir.

42:56.687 --> 42:58.787
I got it.

43:02.159 --> 43:04.726
You two,
keep your heads down
and remember your
training!

43:04.728 --> 43:05.994
We never had
any training!

43:05.995 --> 43:07.261
Well, keep your
heads down!

43:07.264 --> 43:09.064
Consider yourself trained.
This is going to be close.

43:12.403 --> 43:14.269
All right,
you rust buckets.
Let's dance.

43:21.879 --> 43:24.179
Um, can you do that?

43:24.181 --> 43:24.980
Well, apparently.

43:31.155 --> 43:34.089
I am so in love
with her right now.

43:34.091 --> 43:35.824
What?
Nothing.

43:35.826 --> 43:37.759
If we can get
to the north tunnel
before they get to us,

43:37.761 --> 43:39.495
I can trip
the security door.

43:39.496 --> 43:41.230
Isabella, can you
give us more throttle?

43:41.232 --> 43:43.098
It's all the way in, sir!

43:43.100 --> 43:46.001
All right, hang tough.
This is going to get
hairy.

43:52.009 --> 43:53.508
Can we make those turns
at this speed?

43:53.510 --> 43:54.009
Well, we're about
to find out.

44:09.460 --> 44:10.959
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

44:15.266 --> 44:17.132
There it is.
We should be okay
if we can hold off
these...

44:24.341 --> 44:25.674
Can we do that?

44:25.675 --> 44:27.008
No. Keep your head down.

44:37.855 --> 44:39.288
We're slowing down, sir!

44:39.290 --> 44:40.489
Keep it on the floor!

44:40.491 --> 44:43.025
It's on the floor.

44:43.027 --> 44:45.527
There's too much track,
sir.
I don't think we're going
to make it!

44:45.529 --> 44:47.129
Everyone,
to the front now!

44:47.131 --> 44:48.297
We're going to have
to cut loose these...

44:50.501 --> 44:51.900
The motor's overheating!

44:58.142 --> 44:59.574
Sorry, guys.
You're on your own.

45:04.248 --> 45:05.847
PHINEAS 2D:
What are you doing?

45:05.849 --> 45:08.083
My job.
Protecting you two.

45:08.085 --> 45:10.385
We've got to go back
and help them.

45:10.387 --> 45:11.853
That's not our fight.

45:11.855 --> 45:13.221
But you just
abandoned them!

45:13.223 --> 45:15.057
We could have made it!
We could have all made it!

45:15.059 --> 45:16.625
Or we could have
all been captured,

45:16.626 --> 45:18.192
and I wasn't going
to take that chance.

45:18.195 --> 45:20.195
These are
the tough choices, people.

45:20.197 --> 45:21.530
Somebody's got to
be the adult here.

45:21.532 --> 45:23.432
You two are safe,
and that's what's
important.

45:23.434 --> 45:24.066
But... But... But...
End of discussion.

45:34.178 --> 45:38.347
Man, I had my heart set
on those nachos.

45:38.349 --> 45:40.349
Look, mysterious force,

45:40.350 --> 45:42.350
I feel a little awkward
talking to you

45:42.353 --> 45:46.521
since I didn't believe
in you at first because,
you know, it's crazy.

45:46.523 --> 45:49.291
But then I saw you
eat my friend,

45:49.293 --> 45:53.095
so I've made
a little shrine here.

45:53.097 --> 45:57.332
It's nice.
There's a banana and...
Oh! Mr. Miggins.

45:57.334 --> 46:01.370
So I hope
this makes up for the
whole disbelief thing.

46:02.506 --> 46:04.906
Are we, uh...
Are we good?

46:07.277 --> 46:11.980
Now you have no choice
but to fix my machine.

46:11.982 --> 46:13.281
No.
That's not one
of your choices.

46:13.283 --> 46:14.583
Fix the machine!
No.

46:14.585 --> 46:17.119
Can I...
Can I say something?

46:17.121 --> 46:19.488
So, I think I'm up-to-date
on
the whole Perry Agent
thing.

46:19.490 --> 46:21.990
Strangely, that's the
most normal thing that's
happened this afternoon,

46:21.992 --> 46:24.993
but who exactly
is this guy?

46:26.063 --> 46:28.029
Fix it!
No.

46:28.031 --> 46:31.199
Look, I would make myself
do it but apparently
he's an idiot.

46:31.201 --> 46:33.001
Hey!
Fix the machine!

46:33.003 --> 46:34.653
No.

46:34.654 --> 46:36.304
All right, then,
you've forced my hand.

46:39.243 --> 46:40.609
Fix the machine!

46:40.611 --> 46:42.344
No.
Really?

46:42.346 --> 46:44.312
When I was your age,
I did anything
a puppet told me to do.

46:44.314 --> 46:45.647
How old do you think
we are?

46:45.649 --> 46:47.549
I don't know.
One, two?

46:47.551 --> 46:49.801
You know,
it's hard to tell
with the one eye.

46:49.802 --> 46:52.052
Anyway, I don't know
why you're being
so uncooperative.

46:52.055 --> 46:54.489
All I'm asking you to do
is make my machine work

46:54.491 --> 46:57.659
so I can invade
and conquer your world
and enslave your loved
ones.

46:57.661 --> 46:59.961
See, that's just it.

46:59.963 --> 47:01.997
Why would we do something
that would lead to our
own self-destruction?

47:01.999 --> 47:03.999
Self-destruction?
Self-destruct...
Wait a...

47:04.001 --> 47:05.751
Wait, that's it.
I remember now.

47:05.752 --> 47:07.502
They took out my
self-destruct button.

47:07.504 --> 47:09.704
I don't know why
I put it back in,
but here.

47:09.706 --> 47:12.974
I'll just rewire this,
like so, and there.

47:14.478 --> 47:18.680
It's working! It's
working!
It's functioning properly!

47:18.682 --> 47:21.683
Well, look who just
became redundant.

47:23.020 --> 47:24.286
Send them
to their doom!

47:25.689 --> 47:26.054
Yes, her, too.

47:28.091 --> 47:29.624
Yes, yes, everyone.

47:29.626 --> 47:31.693
Doom, doom,
doom and doom.
Doom!

47:31.695 --> 47:33.528
Jinx!
You owe me three sodas.

47:33.530 --> 47:34.729
Okay, doom for him, too.

47:35.532 --> 47:37.666
What? But I'm you!

47:37.668 --> 47:39.668
Doom!

47:39.670 --> 47:42.671
Wow, if I had
a nickel for every time
I was doomed by a puppet,

47:42.673 --> 47:44.673
I'd have two nickels.

47:44.675 --> 47:46.741
Which isn't a lot.
But it's weird that
it happened twice, right?

47:55.719 --> 47:59.087
<i> Welcome, doomed guests.</i>

47:59.089 --> 48:01.623
<i> Come on, keep trudging.</i>
<i> Doom is thataway.</i>

48:07.564 --> 48:11.099
I would say, so far,
adulthood gets about
a three.

48:11.101 --> 48:13.168
You know,
this may be as
good as it gets.

48:16.240 --> 48:19.441
<i> And now for my all-time</i>
<i> favorite game.</i>

48:19.443 --> 48:21.276
<i> Poke the Goozim</i>
<i> with a stick.</i>

48:22.679 --> 48:24.446
<i> Surrounded by lava.</i>

48:24.448 --> 48:27.315
<i> My second favorite game</i>
<i> is backgammon. Love it!</i>

48:27.317 --> 48:29.751
Whoa! Whoa!
Hold the phone.
I could be useful.

48:29.753 --> 48:32.437
What if you need a kidney

48:32.438 --> 48:35.122
or a stand-in
for boring functions
you have to attend?

48:35.125 --> 48:36.191
Or another kidney?

48:37.361 --> 48:38.527
<i> Doom!</i>

48:38.529 --> 48:40.529
Pooh.

48:45.035 --> 48:46.067
(ROARING)

48:49.406 --> 48:52.474
<i> Cranky, cranky, cranky.</i>
<i> Oh, I love the crank!</i>

48:58.815 --> 49:00.649
I'll be honest, Ferb.

49:00.650 --> 49:02.484
I'm having a hard time
putting a positive spin
on this.

49:02.486 --> 49:05.353
Blah, blah, blah,
two-car garage, etcetera.

49:05.355 --> 49:06.087
Yeah? Well,
welcome to my life!

49:08.692 --> 49:11.259
Whoa, deja vu-ish.

49:13.430 --> 49:15.430
Perry, check out
that guard!

49:16.533 --> 49:17.666
Keys!

49:24.374 --> 49:25.674
Cool! Look out!

49:29.479 --> 49:32.180
Ow! Is this the plan?

49:32.182 --> 49:33.932
Tell me
this isn't the plan!

49:33.933 --> 49:35.683
NORMBOT: <i> You are</i>
<i> tampering</i>
<i> with the property of...</i>

49:35.686 --> 49:36.751
<i> Let's make omelets!</i>

49:42.125 --> 49:43.491
DOOFENSHMIRTZ: Can you
get a little more lift
out of this thing?

49:43.493 --> 49:44.910
I think I just
bruised a kidney.

49:44.911 --> 49:46.328
NORM 2D:
<i> My bicycle is missing!</i>

49:48.098 --> 49:49.264
(ALL SCREAMING)

49:53.437 --> 49:54.603
(ALL CHEERING)

49:55.472 --> 49:56.538
(ALL SIGH)

50:00.744 --> 50:02.344
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

50:09.620 --> 50:11.119
<i> Yes! Go, Goozim!</i>

50:11.121 --> 50:12.787
<i> It's muffin time, sir.</i>
<i> Already?</i>

50:24.568 --> 50:28.203
Okay, I see where
you're going with this...

50:28.205 --> 50:30.138
I officially prefer
our dimension!

50:30.140 --> 50:30.872
(SCREAMS)

50:33.710 --> 50:35.577
DOOFENSHMIRTZ:
This may not be the
best time to tell you,

50:35.579 --> 50:39.347
but I actually flunked
jungle gym in grade
school.

50:39.349 --> 50:41.616
I just couldn't get the
hang
of all the climbing...
(SCREAMS)

50:50.494 --> 50:52.761
Oh, great,
you caught it!
Unlock me!

50:52.763 --> 50:54.262
Are you even
paying attention?

50:55.732 --> 50:58.266
That's right.
It can wait. Later!

51:04.574 --> 51:07.175
<i> More guards!</i>

51:07.177 --> 51:08.677
<i> It's muffin time, sir!</i>
<i> You're broken!</i>

51:18.221 --> 51:19.521
(THUMPING)

51:25.896 --> 51:27.529
(GRUNTING)

51:48.919 --> 51:51.586
Yay, other dimension
Candace!

51:51.588 --> 51:53.588
Phineas!

51:54.524 --> 51:56.691
Catch!

52:02.699 --> 52:05.667
(GASPS) The remote!

52:07.370 --> 52:08.570
(ROARING)

52:10.707 --> 52:12.707
Perry, let go!

52:13.944 --> 52:17.545
What?
No, no, don't let go.

52:17.547 --> 52:19.013
Perry! Trust me!

52:19.015 --> 52:20.014
CANDACE:
Two words! La-va!

52:21.685 --> 52:22.784
Trust me!

52:43.707 --> 52:45.039
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

52:53.750 --> 52:55.049
(ROARS)

52:56.686 --> 52:58.419
(WHIMPERING)

53:01.291 --> 53:05.326
<i> They opened another</i>
<i> portal!</i>
<i> Go after them!</i>

53:05.328 --> 53:07.529
<i> And her!</i>
<i> That banshee</i>
<i> screaming girl.</i>

53:07.531 --> 53:08.530
<i> Get her, too!</i>

53:10.000 --> 53:12.333
Thanks,
Perry the Platypus.

53:12.335 --> 53:14.369
NORMBOT:
<i> Stop where you are.</i>
<i> You cannot leave.</i>

53:14.371 --> 53:16.337
<i> I use aggression</i>
<i> to mask my insecurities!</i>

53:18.375 --> 53:19.507
The portal!

53:22.979 --> 53:25.613
<i> Boy, I could go</i>
<i> for a lemonade.</i>

53:26.716 --> 53:27.916
(GRUNTING)

53:29.753 --> 53:30.518
NORMBOT:
<i> The portal closed, sir.</i>

53:30.520 --> 53:33.087
<i> Oh, pooh.</i>

53:33.089 --> 53:35.623
<i> Oh, well. Time to</i>
<i> start the invasion!</i>

53:35.625 --> 53:37.091
<i> And somebody</i>
<i> get me a muffin!</i>

53:37.093 --> 53:37.959
<i> But it's not</i>
<i> muffin time, sir!</i>

53:44.701 --> 53:46.935
All right, follow me.
We're going around
clockwise.

53:58.615 --> 54:02.116
MAN:
<i> ♪ If there's no</i>
<i> hospitality</i>
<i> Just get out of town</i>

54:02.118 --> 54:04.452
<i> ♪ You can't be</i>
<i> lying on formality</i>
<i> And saying...</i>

54:04.454 --> 54:06.988
