01:09:58.143 --> 01:10:00.310
Mom, if you care
one iota about me,

01:10:00.312 --> 01:10:03.446
your family, and your
city,
you'll come outside
with me right now!

01:10:03.448 --> 01:10:05.281
Well, I guess I could
use some more popcorn.

01:10:05.283 --> 01:10:06.949
Great! Come on,
come on, come on,
come on!

01:10:09.821 --> 01:10:12.588
Ferb! Bro, I just hit
the best home run ever!

01:10:23.001 --> 01:10:26.903
Now, tremble before me!

01:10:26.905 --> 01:10:30.306
No, I'm down here.
See, one last trick
up my sleeve.

01:10:30.308 --> 01:10:34.043
It's me! I'm the trick
up my own sleeves,

01:10:34.045 --> 01:10:36.612
'cause I'm in the sleeve,
get it?

01:10:36.614 --> 01:10:40.216
(SIGHS)
Pearls before swine.

01:10:40.218 --> 01:10:43.286
Hope you got your 3-D
glasses
'cause I'm coming at you!

01:10:45.490 --> 01:10:46.389
Yeah!

01:10:46.391 --> 01:10:46.589
Hey!

01:10:49.327 --> 01:10:52.295
What? I'm kind of
in the middle of
something here.

01:10:52.297 --> 01:10:55.431
I got a little something
just for you.

01:10:57.369 --> 01:10:58.968
Here.

01:11:02.474 --> 01:11:03.540
Choo-Choo!

01:11:03.541 --> 01:11:04.607
Yeah, it's mine.
See, I told you
I never lost it.

01:11:04.609 --> 01:11:07.510
It was in a box
in my pantry labeled
"VHS tapes."

01:11:07.512 --> 01:11:10.246
Go figure.
Anyway, you can have it.

01:11:10.248 --> 01:11:13.116
I can't believe it!
Choo-Choo, it is you!

01:11:13.118 --> 01:11:19.021
Heart melting,
back-story resolving,
evilness diminishing.

01:11:19.023 --> 01:11:20.923
It's the least I can do.

01:11:20.925 --> 01:11:22.492
You know,
I don't even know
what I was thinking

01:11:22.494 --> 01:11:24.594
with the whole
evil robots thing.

01:11:24.596 --> 01:11:27.363
Actually,
when I look around,
I'm really embarrassed.

01:11:27.365 --> 01:11:29.465
Let me clean this up.
Look! Self-destruct
button.

01:11:29.467 --> 01:11:32.235
Ah, you.

01:11:32.237 --> 01:11:33.369
Yeah. Here we go!

01:11:39.544 --> 01:11:42.412
Come on, come on, come on!
Come on, hurry, hurry!

01:11:42.414 --> 01:11:45.047
Do I even need to say
"there's nothing there"
anymore?

01:11:45.049 --> 01:11:47.450
Mom, you can say it
all you want.
There's nothing there!

01:11:47.452 --> 01:11:50.486
Whoo-hoo! I did it,
I saved the world!

01:11:52.056 --> 01:11:52.989
You can go back
to your movie now.

01:11:58.596 --> 01:12:00.463
Yeah, you know what?
We're totally cool now.

01:12:00.465 --> 01:12:02.265
I'm just gonna go
return to my home

01:12:02.267 --> 01:12:04.467
and live out
the rest of my days
with my Choo-Choo.

01:12:04.469 --> 01:12:06.102
Okay then, ciao!

01:12:06.104 --> 01:12:07.703
Home. It's good
to be... Uh-oh.

01:12:10.375 --> 01:12:12.992
Book him, ladies.

01:12:12.993 --> 01:12:15.610
You know, my crimes
against humanity had just
completely slipped my
mind.

01:12:15.613 --> 01:12:18.548
Hey! Did you guys
just see that?
I saved Danville!

01:12:18.550 --> 01:12:19.982
Good job, soldier.

01:12:19.984 --> 01:12:21.717
So what'll you do now?

01:12:21.719 --> 01:12:24.620
Wow, I haven't thought
of anything but busting
Doofenshmirtz for years.

01:12:24.622 --> 01:12:26.539
I don't know.

01:12:26.540 --> 01:12:28.457
Well, I know what
interests I'd pursue.

01:12:28.460 --> 01:12:30.860
Hey! Here you all are.

01:12:30.861 --> 01:12:33.261
I'll take that
under consideration.
What about you, Candace?

01:12:33.264 --> 01:12:35.298
You know,
after all of this,

01:12:35.300 --> 01:12:37.533
I'm gonna give myself
a little more time
to be young.

01:12:37.535 --> 01:12:39.101
It's not such
a bad place to be.

01:12:39.103 --> 01:12:41.437
You know what?
Me, too.

01:12:41.439 --> 01:12:44.273
Hey, I just wanted to
say thanks for telling us
all about summer,

01:12:44.275 --> 01:12:46.476
you know,
opening our horizons,

01:12:46.478 --> 01:12:48.344
and teaching Ferb
classical guitar.

01:12:48.346 --> 01:12:49.412
(NOTES PLAYING)

01:12:53.685 --> 01:12:55.251
(CHATTERING)

01:12:55.253 --> 01:12:57.420
Hey! It's our Perry!
Perry!

01:12:57.422 --> 01:13:00.523
Looks like
the evil was fried
right out of him.

01:13:00.525 --> 01:13:02.041
Sorry he's mostly
made of metal now.

01:13:02.042 --> 01:13:03.558
Are you kidding?
That makes him
extra cool!

01:13:03.561 --> 01:13:06.095
Thanks so much, guys.

01:13:06.097 --> 01:13:07.597
I'm glad
we could help.

01:13:12.337 --> 01:13:14.737
Man, this has been
the greatest day ever.

01:13:14.739 --> 01:13:16.405
Imagine how much fun
we can have together

01:13:16.407 --> 01:13:18.274
now that we know
you're a secret agent.

01:13:18.276 --> 01:13:21.744
Yes, yes,
the next 15 minutes
should be a real hoot.

01:13:21.746 --> 01:13:24.714
Well, then, of course,
Agent P will be
sent away forever.

01:13:24.716 --> 01:13:26.699
What?
You didn't know?

01:13:26.700 --> 01:13:28.683
Didn't he give you
a pamphlet?
We threw it away.

01:13:28.686 --> 01:13:30.319
Does anyone
read those things?

01:13:30.321 --> 01:13:32.088
I tried to warn you, sir.

01:13:32.090 --> 01:13:35.258
Kids, I'm sorry
but now that Agent P's
cover has been blown,

01:13:35.260 --> 01:13:37.226
you won't be allowed
to see him anymore.

01:13:37.228 --> 01:13:40.129
That's why
you didn't want us
to know your secret.

01:13:40.131 --> 01:13:41.797
So we'll never see
Perry again?

01:13:41.799 --> 01:13:43.366
There has to be
another way.

01:13:43.368 --> 01:13:46.202
Sorry, Phineas.
It isn't safe.
You know too much.

01:13:46.204 --> 01:13:49.272
Now I never wished
so much that I could
unknow something.

01:13:49.274 --> 01:13:50.740
Sir, maybe
there is a way.

01:13:50.742 --> 01:13:53.743
What about
Dr. Doofenshmirtz's
Amnesianator?

01:13:53.745 --> 01:13:56.512
I never built
an Amnesianator.

01:13:56.514 --> 01:13:59.148
I think I'd remember
building something
like that.

01:13:59.149 --> 01:14:01.783
Well, that might work.
But you'd all have to
agree.

01:14:01.786 --> 01:14:05.555
So our choice is to either
forget the best day ever,

01:14:05.557 --> 01:14:07.657
forget the biggest
adventure
we've ever had,

01:14:07.659 --> 01:14:09.525
and forget
meeting Agent P,

01:14:09.527 --> 01:14:12.395
or remember today,
but never see Perry again?

01:14:13.331 --> 01:14:15.264
Well, we've had
a lot of great days.

01:14:15.266 --> 01:14:17.833
But we only have
one Perry.

01:14:17.835 --> 01:14:19.168
Agreed.

01:14:19.170 --> 01:14:20.836
ALL: Yeah!

01:14:20.838 --> 01:14:23.506
MONOGRAM:
All right, everybody.
Tall kids in the back.

01:14:23.508 --> 01:14:24.674
Just need to do
a little more
programming here

01:14:24.676 --> 01:14:26.776
and we'll be
ready to roll.

01:14:26.778 --> 01:14:28.678
Hey, buddy, Ferb and I
just wanted to say
our goodbyes.

01:14:28.680 --> 01:14:31.514
You know, we thought
we'd finally met
the real you

01:14:31.516 --> 01:14:34.083
when we found out
you were Agent P,

01:14:34.084 --> 01:14:36.651
but the fact is,
pet, secret agent,
they're both the real you.

01:14:36.654 --> 01:14:39.088
You are now and
always have been

01:14:39.090 --> 01:14:41.724
a great pet
and a great friend.

01:14:41.726 --> 01:14:44.160
We're gonna
miss you, Agent P.

01:14:45.530 --> 01:14:46.796
I love you, pal.

01:14:46.798 --> 01:14:48.564
Sir, are you crying?

01:14:48.566 --> 01:14:49.632
No, I'm sweating
through my eyes.

01:14:49.634 --> 01:14:52.735
Okay, sir.
We're ready.

01:14:52.737 --> 01:14:54.503
Okay, Karl.
We're set.

01:14:56.274 --> 01:14:59.208
